inline_comments.message:
If this kube api endpoint returns empty list is the assumption of http and https 80 and 443 still valid?

If yes then I would deobfuscate the below code to a more readable:

if svc:
 for item ...
   if item.metadata...
     return http_port,https_port
 else:
   return (80,443)

Other issue is with the logic of the 'for' statement: if "if item.metadata.name == K8S_INGRESS_NS" evaluates to 'true' only once then it should contain loop braking statement, otherwise http{s}_port returns it's values from the last evaluation of this statement to 'true' which is either side effect or somehow obfuscated logic.
